8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
9 {New Section 1. (a) Whenever an election is required for the
10 issuance of bonds by any municipality, such election shall be called and
11 held on the date of the next primary or general election, as specified in
12 the resolution calling such election. Any law that specifies an election
13 date for such election shall take precedence over the provisions of this
14 section and such election shall be held on the specified election date.
15 (b) No municipality shall call or hold more than one bond election
16 at a time other than on the same date as a primary or general election
17 within any one calendar year. The provisions of this subsection shall not
18 prohibit the planning for or consideration of any bond election during
19 the period between authorized bond elections, nor shall this subsection
20 prohibit notice or other preparation for election during such period.
21 This subsection shall not apply to bond elections held for the purpose of
22 replacing, or repairing and equipping municipal buildings or facilities
23 destroyed or substantially damaged by fire, windstorm, flood or other
24 casualty.
25 (c) This section shall be a part of and supplemental the general
26 bond laws of this state.}
27 Section 1. {Sec. 2.} K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 10-120 is hereby amended to
28 read as follows: 10-120. (a) Whenever an election is required for the
29 issuance of bonds for any purpose by any municipality other than an
30 irrigation district or where a different procedure for giving notice of the
31 election is specifically provided by law, upon compliance with the legal
32 requirements necessary and precedent to the call for the election, the
33 proper municipal officers shall call an election. The election shall be

