6 (b) Notice of the election shall be published in a newspaper of
7 general circulation in the municipality once each week for two
8 consecutive weeks. The first publication shall be not less than 21 days
9 prior to the election. Notice of the election shall also be published on the
10 website of the county election office of any county where the election is
11 to be conducted. Such notice shall be published not less than 21 days
12 prior to the election and shall remain on the website until the day after
13 the election. The notice shall set forth the time and place of holding the
14 election and the purpose for which the bonds are to be issued and shall
15 be signed by the county election officer. The election shall be held at the
16 usual place of holding elections and shall be conducted by the officers or
17 persons provided by law for holding elections in the municipality.
18 Sec. 2. {3.} K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 25-1115 is hereby amended to read as
19 follows: 25-1115. (a) "General election" means the elections held on the
20 Tuesday following the first Monday in November of both even-numbered
21 and odd-numbered years, and in the case of an election of any officers to
22 fill vacancies held on a date other than the Tuesday following the first
23 Monday in November, the election at which any such officer is finally
24 elected.
25 (b) "Primary election" means the elections held on the first
26 Tuesday in August of both even-numbered and odd-numbered years and
27 any other preliminary election held on a date other than the first
28 Tuesday in August at which part of the candidates for election to any
29 national, state, county, city, school or other municipal office are
30 eliminated by the process of the election but at which no officer is finally
31 elected.
32 (c) "Special election" means any election that is not a general or
33 primary election, including, but not limited to, any mail ballot election
34 conducted pursuant to K.S.A. 25-431 et seq., and amendments thereto. A
35 special election shall not be held within 45 days of a general or primary
36 election but may be held on the same day as a general or primary election
37 held on the first Tuesday after the first Monday in April of any year or on
38 the same day as a general or primary election.
